  "title": "SITE MANAGER",
  "description": "<p><strong>Job Description</strong></p>\n<h4><strong>1. Project &amp; Site Management</strong></h4>\n<ul>\n  <li>Manage all on-site tunnelling activities (excavation, lining, ground support, TBM operation, etc.).</li>\n  <li>Coordinate with project engineers, design teams, subcontractors, and clients.</li>\n  <li>Plan daily and weekly work programs, ensuring manpower, materials, and equipment are available.</li>\n  <li>Monitor progress against schedule and implement corrective measures for delays.</li>\n</ul>\n<h4><strong>2. Safety &amp; Compliance</strong></h4>\n<ul>\n  <li>Enforce strict adherence to health, safety, and environmental (HSE) standards.</li>\n  <li>Conduct regular site safety inspections and risk assessments.</li>\n  <li>Ensure compliance with tunnelling regulations (e.g., confined space, ground control, ventilation).</li>\n</ul>\n<h4><strong>3. Quality Control</strong></h4>\n<ul>\n  <li>Oversee testing and inspection of ground support, concrete lining, and waterproofing works.</li>\n  <li>Ensure all works comply with design specifications, drawings, and QA/QC requirements.</li>\n  <li>Maintain documentation for audits and handover.</li>\n</ul>\n<h4><strong>4. Personnel &amp; Subcontractor Supervision</strong></h4>\n<ul>\n  <li>Supervise tunnelling crews (miners, TBM operators, engineers, etc.).</li>\n  <li>Manage subcontractor performance and productivity.</li>\n  <li>Lead daily coordination and toolbox meetings.</li>\n</ul>\n<h4><strong>5. Reporting &amp; Documentation</strong></h4>\n<ul>\n  <li>Prepare daily, weekly, and monthly progress reports.</li>\n  <li>Track resources, materials, and productivity data.</li>\n  <li>Communicate updates to the Project Manager and client representatives.</li>\n</ul>\n<h4><strong>6. Technical &amp; Logistical Coordination</strong></h4>\n<ul>\n  <li>Coordinate tunnel excavation sequences and spoil removal.</li>\n  <li>Plan logistics for material delivery, mucking, ventilation, lighting, and utilities.</li>\n  <li>Troubleshoot site and technical issues in real time.</li>\n</ul>\n<p><strong>Requirements</strong></p>\n<ul>\n  <li>Bachelor’s degree in Civil Engineering, Construction Management, or related field (or relevant experience).</li>\n  <li>More than 5 years of experience in tunnelling construction.</li>\n  <li>Previous involvement in large-scale infrastructure projects (e.g., rail, metro, utility tunnels) is an asset.</li>\n  <li>Certifications: PMP, OSHA/CSCS, or tunnel-specific safety training may be required depending on location.</li>\n  <li>Able to working 6 days, including  Saturday or Sunday</li>\n</ul>",
